==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hearten
<hw>Heart"en</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rt"'n)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Heart</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To encourage; to animate; to
incite or stimulate the courage of; to embolden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Hearten</qex> those that fight in your defense.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To restore fertility or strength to, as to
land.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heartener</ent>⟦br⟧
